// Step 1: Declare the array with 3 rows
int[][] jaggedArray = new int[3][];

// Step 2: Initialize each row with different sizes
jaggedArray[0] = new int[2]; // Row 0 has 2 columns
jaggedArray[1] = new int[5]; // Row 1 has 5 columns
jaggedArray[2] = new int[3]; // Row 2 has 3 columns


Jagged array is efficient when there is irregualr data

A real life example of this, is our college timetable , where we have different amount of lectures on each day
so information will be stored better in jagged array 
